src/lib/components/DashWebsocketComponen.description:
ExampleComponent is an example component.
It takes a property, `label`, and
displays it.
It renders an input with the property `value`
which is editable by the user.

state.description: This websocket state (in the readyState prop) and associated information.

message.description: When messages are received, this property is updated with the message content.

error.description: This property is set with the content of the onerror event.

send.description: When this property is set, a message is sent with its content.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.
